# 5. Types of Two Pointer Patterns

---

# Pattern 1: Opposite Direction

Most common.

```java
left = 0;
right = n - 1;
```

Move towards each other.

```text
1 2 3 4 5 6

L         R
```

Applications:

- Pair Sum
- Palindrome
- Container With Most Water
- 3Sum

---

# Pattern 2: Same Direction

```java
slow = 0;
fast = 0;
```

Both move forward.

```text
0 1 2 3 4 5

S
F
```

Applications:

- Remove Duplicates
- Remove Elements
- Move Zeros

---

# Pattern 3: Fast and Slow Pointer

Used in Linked Lists.

```java
slow = head;
fast = head;
```

```java
slow = slow.next;
fast = fast.next.next;
```

Applications:

- Cycle Detection
- Middle Node
- Happy Number

---

# Pattern 4: Sliding Window

Special case of Two Pointers.

```java
left
right
```

Both move forward.

Applications:

- Longest Substring
- Maximum Sum Subarray
- K Distinct Characters

---

# Pattern 5: Partitioning

Used in Quick Sort.

```java
left++;
right--;
```

Applications:

- Quick Sort
- Dutch National Flag

